main event: A bright star-like object was observed moving in the northwest sky over Morehead, Kentucky on July 27, 1963.
interesting points: The object was about the size of a small star, hovering and moving slowly.
The object appeared to be as bright as the small stars in the sky.
The object passed beside a bright star and moved down the valley.
The observer could not determine the exact altitude or character of the object.
There was a small airstrip about 8 miles west of the observation location.
witnesses: one observer, a student at radio station WMOR
photographs: no photographs included in the report
